The paper focuses on a computer vision task of segmenting finger bones, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a semi-supervised self-taught deep learning framework, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study also involves medical imaging, which could place it under the sub-category of medical imaging (cs.MED). Finally, the paper involves the use of a teacher-student model, which could suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR) as well.
